extraOptions.highlights:
If you’re seeking an adventure and an experience unlike any other, look no further than Delta 105. Our military theme park is a unique recreational destination that takes visitors on a journey through the life of an army camp, offering a glimpse into what makes a jawan.

Our expertly designed experience caters to all age groups and provides a perfect day-long outing on the outskirts of the city. Visitors can indulge in various recreational activities and challenges that are not only enriching but also incredibly fun. From team outings to leadership training, family day, social gatherings, or school outings, Delta 105 is the perfect destination to create unforgettable memories that last a lifetime.

packages.content:
Kids: INR 1199 plus GST (between 3ft & 4ft)

The Activities at Delta 105 are unique, full of fun, adventure and suited for all age groups: You may not be able to finish all activities in one day.

ARMY INSPIRED FUN ACTIVITIES:
  • Longest & highest Zipline in NCR: cruise on a 224 meters Zipline from a height of 40 meters.
  • Grenade Range: It takes strength to throw hand grenades unlike shown in the Bollywood movies. You can try your hands at these dummy grenades which are almost exact replica of real ones.
  • Paint Ball : Guests above 15 years of age can play by paying Rs.300 for 30 pellets per person.
  • Race with Battle Load: A soldier carries an average of 23 kgs of battle load on him and travels for long distances, as long as 40 kms. Try wearing the haversacks filled with 5, 10 or 20 kgs of sand and run for 100 meters. You will get some view of hardships our brave soldiers faces.
  • Crawl Trench: Wear actual army uniform and military helmets. And then try to pass through crawl trench made of barbed wires.
  • Firing Range: Each guest will fire three rounds on a figure 11 targets using paintball guns.
  • Pagal Gymkhana: Fun activities like Sack race, Tug of War, Two Leg race, etc
  • War Zone: Depiction of international border with bunkers & trenches. Briefing by An Ex-Serviceman with use of original equipment like helmets, Binocular, etc.
  • Obstacle Course for Adults (and smaller one for kids also): The guests will have to cross 8 obstacles and record their best time (the best time so far is 2 minutes 30 seconds): These are simple yet need to think before attempting.
  • Assault Course: Junior Commando For Kids
  • Walk through Army Heritage: Guests get to see the various tools, equipment, uniforms, etc used by the Armed Forces of India.
  • Sarva-Dharm-Sthal or MMGC (Mandir, Masjid, Gurudwara, Church) complex: Army is a true example of communal harmony and the youth of country needs to be sensitized about it. The MMG Complex will show them the true secular fabric of the nation.
  • Briefing Zone: Clear and crisp instructions are hallmark of an Army Briefing. The guests will be briefed on a 3D model about the camp, Dos & Don’ts, etc. It will be done before their visit.
  • Activity Zone: Guests can indulge in following activities like Understanding National Flag, Knot Tying, etc
  • Story telling by Veterans: Most Army men get a chance to serve in warzones like Kashmir or North East. The guests can hear their hair raising stories and get inspired.
  • War memorial: Pay your respect to the soldiers who died for the country.
  • Army tents: Tents made of parachutes used by Indian Air Force are erected as rest zones. Similarly, tents used by Army are also displayed.
  • Kidzone : Rides, swings and trampoline. This area is reserved for toddlers & young kids
  • Sports Arena: Sports play an important role in the Armed Forces and an hour is reserved every evening for all troops. The sports arena at Delta 105 has field for Football, Volleyball, cricket, etc.
INTERACTIVE FUN ACTIVITIES
  • Smash the Glass activity
  • Basket ball
  • Archery
  • Dart Shooting
  • Gun Shoot
  • Mehnedi
  • Magician
  • Nut Dance
  • Horse & Camel Cart Rides
DJ FLOOR – THROUGHOUT THE DAY

Tasty and Nutritious food made in a hygienically environment is served as set menu in Delta Mess. Bar-Be-Que and Dinner is served in tent complex. Water used to prepare food is from RO plant.

BREAKFAST (9:30AM – 11AM)
Stuffed Parantha, white makhan and Dahi
Poori and Bhaji
Poha or Upma
Tea

LUNCH (1PM – 3PM)
Assorted Roti
Rice
Rajma
Paneer Vegetable
Seasonal Vegetable
Chowmein
Raita
Gulab Jamun or Halwa
Green Salad

REGIMENT FOOD (11AM – 5PM)
Makke and Bajre ki roti with desi ghee
Sarson Ka Saag or any Seasonal Vegetable
Kadi
Khichdi
Choorma
Gud, Lassi, Chatni

ALL DAY SNACKS (11AM – 5PM)
Assorted Pakoras
Tea
Any dessert like Jalebi, etc

packages.title: Adults Package

nodes.title: Smoking is prohibited within the premises, in compliance with local laws.
Sale and consumption of alcohol, including adherence to legal drinking age requirements and responsible service practices.
Pets are not allowed on the premises.
Parking is available. Guests are requested to park only in authorized and dedicated parking areas of the venue.
Outside food and beverages are not allowed.
Lost and Found items can be reclaimed only after documentation and verification of the guest.
Guests are required to respect the property and cover any damages caused by them during their visit.
Do not sit at tables that are already reserved.
Arms and ammunition are not allowed inside the premises.
Provision of Wheelchair for senior citizen and physically challenged person only.

data.title: Delta 105 – Military Theme Park
data.content: The camp is set up in 20 acre of land, completely lush green. All the activities are inspired from the Indian Army. Theme park has been started by a retired army personnel Major Dinesh Sharma along with jawans from his regiment. You can spend a Day or you can also stay in our Luxury tents. All precautions against COVID are being taken (we call it military like safety).
